    {
      "text": "## Fix Plan\nThe `ExecutionLoop` service (`src/services/execution_loop.ts`) already implements robust lifecycle management (`handleSuccess`, `handleFailure`).\n\n**Proposed Changes**:\n1.  **Refactor `src/main.ts`**:\n    *   Initialize `ExecutionLoop` service.\n    *   In the `planWatcher` callback, instead of manually parsing and executing, delegate to `ExecutionLoop.processTask(planPath)`.\n    *   *Note*: `ExecutionLoop` expects to own the lifecycle. We need to ensure `initGitBranch` behavior is correct for the `FileWatcher` context (since `RequestProcessor` might have already done some git work, or maybe not. `PlanExecutor` handles branch creation inside `execute`? No, `ExecutionLoop` handles it before calling `executeCore`).",
